1041.c.Problem Statement:
}

Na metal has bcc structure and has one valence electron per atom. Find a formula for and estimate the threshold wavelength (in $\AA$ ) for interband transitions (from the lowest to the next higher energy band) in Na metal. Make use of the fact that $k_{\mathrm{F}}$ is appreciably less than $k_{\mathrm{ZB}}$ (the $k$-vector to the zone boundary nearest the origin). The size of the cube edge $a$ in $\mathrm{Na}$ is $4.23 \AA$.

(Princeton $)$
